'''Jesús María Sanz-Serna''' (born 12 June 1953 in [[Valladolid]], Spain) is a mathematician who specializes in applied mathematics. Sanz-Serna pioneered the field of [[geometric integrator|geometric integration]] and wrote the first book on this subject.<ref>{{citation | last1 = Sanz-Serna | first1 = Jesús María | last2 = Calvo | first2 = Mari-Paz | title = Numerical Hamiltonian Problems | publisher = Chapman & Hall | isbn = 0-412-54290-0 | year = 1994}}</ref>  From 1998 to 2006, he was rector of the [[University of Valladolid]].<ref>[http://sanzserna.org/cv.php Sanz-Serna's CV]</ref>

He received the inaugural Dahlquist Prize from the [[Society for Industrial and Applied Mathematics]] in 1995<ref>[http://www.siam.org/prizes/sponsored/dahlquist.php Germund Dahlquist Prize] at the SIAM website</ref> and became one of the inaugural [[fellow]]s of the [[American Mathematical Society]] in 2012.<ref>[http://www.ams.org/profession/fellows-list List of Fellows of the American Mathematical Society], retrieved 2015-01-18.</ref> His 60th birthday was celebrated at the 2013 International Conference on Scientific Computation and Differential Equations (SciCADE) in Valladolid.<ref>[http://wmatem.eis.uva.es/scicade2013/?pc=5 Sanz-Serna's birthday]</ref>

