'''Konstantin Alexandrovich Posse''' ({{lang-ru|Константин Александрович Поссе}}; September 29, 1847 - August 24, 1928) was a Russian mathematician known for contributions to [[mathematical analysis|analysis]] and in particular [[approximation theory]].<ref name=Steffens>{{cite book|doi=10.1007/0-8176-4475-X|mr=2190312|last=Steffens|first=Karl-Georg|title=The history of approximation theory. From Euler to Bernstein|publisher=Birkhäuser Boston, Inc.|location=Boston, MA|year=2006|isbn=978-0-8176-4353-9|pages=114&ndash;119}}</ref> [[Veniamin Kagan]] and [[D. D. Morduhai-Boltovskoi]] were among his students.

